most_negative_comment: Zero contribution in the central budget for Karnataka. Outrage Farmers in the state are also poor due to drought. It would have been better if the farmers had been loaned off. KPCC general secretary Satish Kumar Adavi expressed his anger by saying that this is a budget that benefits the capitalists by calling it something else. The central government makes announcements but does not implement them. They said that they will bring back black money from abroad as announced earlier. Smart city. Bullet train. Money for everyone.. Why have all these words not been acted upon till now. Looking at the budget announcement, I don't know what to say about them. There are approximately 8 crore people in the country who file income tax returns. Out of which 5 crore people are listed as (NIL). They are not tax payers. The number of tax payers is only 3 crore! In a country with a population of 145 crore, how can a tax exemption that benefits only three crore people be a "bumper gift to the entire middle class", Adavi questioned...

This budget is not for the nation‚Äîit‚Äôs a state election campaign speech in disguise. Instead of addressing India‚Äôs economic concerns, the Finance Minister seems more focused on upcoming elections. 

What Bihar got?
Makhaana Board ‚úÖ

3 Center of excellence (500 cr) ‚úÖ

What has Karnataka lost? üëá
Karnataka‚Äôs rightful ask  as per the 15th Finance Commission Recommendations, 
‚Çπ5,495 Cr Special Grant‚ùå
‚Çπ6,000 Cr State-Specific Grant ‚ùå
‚Çπ1,300 Cr for Urban Local Bodies ‚ùå
‚Çπ826 Cr Health Grants ‚ùå
‚Çπ2,461 Cr MSP Dues ‚ùå

Meanwhile, the union budget in 2024 was a Andhra gets a budget, this year its a Bihar budget, UP in 2026, Gujarat in 2027‚Ä¶ Every year, the Union Budget looks more like a state budget for election-bound regions.
